claim.claim-text:
1. A method of simultaneously participating in multiple contests each comprising a plurality of competitors and corresponding to an event comprising:
a. receiving a list of competitive groups to join on a memory device;
b. selecting a plurality of competitive groups to join, wherein each group of the plurality of competitive groups is a separate competition;
c. participating with the plurality of competitive groups by sending selections related to the event from the memory device to a server; and
d. receiving standings on the memory device from the server, wherein the standings are based on results from the selections, wherein the standings are based on separate scoring in each group of the plurality of competitive groups.

14. A method of conducting multiple contests of skill each comprising a plurality of competitors and corresponding to a single event comprising:
a. generating separate competitive groups related to the single event;
b. coupling to a network with a memory device to participate in the competitive groups;
c. informing a user which of the competitive groups are available for the user to join;
d. joining a selected number of the competitive groups;
e. participating with the competitive groups by sending selections related to the single event from the memory device to a server within the network;
f. storing results and standings on the server, wherein the standings are based on the results and the results are based on the selections, wherein the results are separate for each group of the competitive groups; and
g. transmitting the standings to the memory device.

19. The method as claimed in claim 14 wherein generating competitive groups related to the event further comprises:
a. coupling to the server;
b. selecting a type of contest and additional conditions to be included in the competitive group;
c. adding competitors to the competitive group; and
d. selecting the event for competition by the competitive group.
